entry.answer:
/* specifies a 12 point font for * all ChatZilla messages. */
body.chatzilla-body .msg { font-size: 12pt !important; }
userContent.css rule for 12pt font
If your fonts are way too large or way too small, it is likely a problem with your DPI setting. Check your display preferences. If you're set to use "System Setting", try one of the pre-defined DPI settings instead. In practice, it seems that "System Setting" is almost always wrong. Fixing this will likely help out with web pages that specify font sizes in points, too.
If it's not a DPI thing, you can adjust your font size with a special rule in userContent.css. In the chrome/ subdirectory of your profile directory, create a file called userContent.css, and add the text shown at the right.
